                <h1>Do Misdemeanors Appear on Background Checks?</h1>
                <p>Misdemeanors often appear on background checks, especially if they resulted in a conviction. Employers, landlords, and others may review criminal records that include these offenses. The specifics can vary by state and the type of background check, but it's wise to be aware that misdemeanors can impact job or housing opportunities.</p>
